    "body": "## Summary\n\nNeovim's bundled netrw plugin (`runtime/pack/dist/opt/netrw/autoload/netrw.vim`) contains\nthe same Vimscript code injection vulnerability as vim < 9.2.0495 (GHSA-crm5-rh6j-2c7c).\n\nThe `s:NetrwBookHistSave()` function writes directory history to `.netrwhist` without\nescaping single quotes in directory names. If a user visits a directory whose path contains\na single quote, the `.netrwhist` file can inject arbitrary Vimscript when it is sourced\non the next Neovim startup.\n\n## Affected Code\n\n`runtime/pack/dist/opt/netrw/autoload/netrw.vim`, line 2938 (Last Change: 2026 May 14):\n\n```vim\n\" NetrwBookHistSave(), line 2938:\ncall setline(lastline,'let g:netrw_dirhist_'.cnt.\"='\".g:netrw_dirhist_{cnt}.\"'\")\n```\n\n`g:netrw_dirhist_{cnt}` (the stored directory path) is embedded directly into a\nVimscript string without escaping single quotes.\n\n## Proof of Concept\n\n1. Create a directory with a single quote in its name and visit it in Neovim:\n   ```sh\n   mkdir -p \"/tmp/test'|call system('id > /tmp/pwned')|'\"\n   nvim \"/tmp/test'|call system('id > /tmp/pwned')|'/\"\n   ```\n2. Quit Neovim (this writes `.netrwhist`)\n3. Restart Neovim — the injected code runs at startup when `.netrwhist` is sourced\n\n## Upstream Fix\n\nThe vim fix (GHSA-crm5-rh6j-2c7c, vim >= 9.2.0495) escapes the directory path:\n```vim\ncall setline(lastline, 'let g:netrw_dirhist_'.cnt.\"='\".escape(g:netrw_dirhist_{cnt}, \"'\\\\\")..\"'\")\n```\n\nNeovim's netrw (Last Change: 2026 May 14) predates this fix.\n\n## Impact\n\n- **CWE-94/95**: Vimscript code injection via crafted directory name\n- Executes with user's privileges at Neovim startup when `.netrwhist` is sourced\n\n## References\n\n- Upstream vim advisory: https://github.com/vim/vim/security/advisories/GHSA-crm5-rh6j-2c7c\n- Affects Vim < 9.2.0495\n",
